You need:

  1. Build tools
     1.1 compiler + linker
         Known to work with gcc 3.4.3 and binutils 2.15.94.0.2.2
         You can get gcc from http://www.gnu.org/software/gcc/
         You can get binutils from http://www.gnu.org/software/binutils/
     1.2 GNU Make
         Known to work with GNU Make 3.80
         You can get it from http://www.gnu.org/software/make/
     1.3 pkg-config
         Known to work with pkg-config 0.19
         You can get it from http://pkgconfig.freedesktop.org/wiki/

  2. Libraries
     2.1 GTK+ >= 2.6
         Known to work with GTK+ 2.8.6
         You can get it from http://www.gtk.org/
     2.2 libglade >= 2.0
         Known to work with libglade 2.5.1
         You can get it from http://www.jamesh.id.au/software/libglade/
     2.3 ALSA library
         Known to work with alsa-lib 1.0.9
         You can get it from http://www.alsa-project.org/

To build gmidimonitor simply run GNU make without parameters:

    # make

If you are running BSD, GNU make may be called gmake, so you run it like this:

    # gmake

If everything compiles, you will get gmidimonitor executable in current directory
Copy it wherever you want

Good luck and report bugs